    "description": "<p><strong>Enable Classic Widgets<\/strong><br \/>\n\u2605\u2605\u2605\u2605\u2605<\/p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>esc_attr(Restore and enable the previous WordPress classic widgets settings screens and disables the Gutenberg block editor from managing widgets. No expiration!<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n<p>The WordPress 5.8 turn the classic widget screen into the block-based widget screen. Yes,  Widgets are now blocks and this is going to be available to everyone instantly.<br \/>\nIt will create compatibility issues for many sites.<\/p>\n<p>There are cases where the our plugin will be necessary:<br \/>\n    * Broken themes or quirky output.<br \/>\n    * Users simply preferring the old system.<\/p>\n<p>Our plugin can restore the classic widget screen with just one click.<br \/>\nThere is no other configuration, the classic widgets settings screens are enabled or disabled by either enabling or disabling this plugin.<\/p>\n<p>This feature (restore classic widget) is available also in our WP Tools free plugin with 35 other useful tools:<br \/>\n<a href=\"https:\/\/wordpress.org\/plugins\/wptools\/\" rel=\"ugc\">WP Tools Free Plugin<\/a><\/p>\n<h3>Important<\/h3>\n<p>If you start using the new block-based widgets system, you will lose all of your widget blocks upon activating our plugin.<br \/>\nThere is no going back, so be sure this is what you want. The former blocks will not reappear if you change your mind and deactivate our plugin.<\/p>\n<h3>Demo Video<\/h3>\n<span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/rul3UlJy2B8?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"><\/ifram